EDS Lite — .NET / MAUI port
===========================

This project is a port of "edslite" (Encrypted Data Store lite), an
open-source file/container encryption application for Android, from Java +
native C to C# (.NET 10) + .NET MAUI.

Original work
-------------
edslite is developed by Sovworks and is licensed under the GNU General
Public License, version 2 or later (GPLv2+). The original project provides the
native cryptographic implementations (AES, Serpent, Twofish, GOST, RIPEMD-160,
Whirlpool, and the XTS/CBC modes) and the container/filesystem logic that this
port reproduces.

The native algorithm cores in `native/vendor/` are copied essentially verbatim
from the original project to preserve byte-for-byte data compatibility with
existing containers; their original copyright and licensing are retained.

This port
---------
The C# managed layer, the unified C-ABI shim (`native/src/edscrypto.c`,
`native/include/edscrypto.h`), the .NET build tooling and the MAUI application
in this repository are likewise licensed under GPLv2+ (see the LICENSE file), in
accordance with the license of the original work.

Third-party components carry their own licenses:
  * AES (Brian Gladman implementation), Serpent, Twofish, GOST, RIPEMD-160 and
    Whirlpool reference cores — as distributed with the original edslite.

